sentence: Hi guys , welcome to Thyview Comments . Naa Peru Sharath , Thyview Subscriber . And Here is my non spoiler Review of MissIndia ! Meeru movie choodataniki , ee comment motham chadavaala ante , ippude cheptunna , 75 % general audience ( time pass kosam movie choose vallaki ) ee movie nachadu . 1st half aithe , edho parledhu baane undi anipinchinaa , 2nd half bedisikottindhi . Aa chai ni America lo ela sell chestundi , ela top position ki vastundi ani chaala sepu wait chesa . Jagapathi babu ela challenge chestaaru ani baaga excite ayya . Kaani akkada 2 challenges maatrame untai . Avi kooda antha impact iyyaledhu . Movie motham lo naaku istamaindhi , cameraman maatrame ! Theatrical experience theppinchaadu ! Hatsoff ! Malli , women powerment dialogs kooda over gaa untadhi . Aa dialogs vinte satisfied kaavadam atu unchithe . Ammailu vinte inkaa pogaru gaa aipothaaru . Abbailu aithe mandipothaaru . Avi aadavaallu em thakkuva kaaru ani kaakundaa , magaadu chaep aadadhanikante , anelaa untai . Meeru , ee movie inkaa choosindaka pothe assalu choodadhu ! Final gaa ee movie ki naa rating 2.5 / 5 Thank You guys , See you again !
translation: Hi guys, welcome to Thyview Comments. Naa Peru Sharath, Thyview Subscriber. And Here is my non-spoiler Review of MissIndia! Meeru movie choodataniki, ee comment motham chadavaala ante, ippude cheptunna, 75% general audience (time pass kosam movie choose vallaki) ee movie nachadu. 1st half aithe, edho parledhu baane undi anipinchinaa, 2nd half bedisikottindhi. Aa chai ni America lo ela sell chestundi , ela top position ki vastundi ani chaala sepu wait chesa . Jagapathi babu ela challenge chestaaru ani baaga excite ayya . Kaani akkada 2 challenges maatrame untai . Avi kooda antha impact iyyaledhu. Movie motham lo naaku istamaindhi, cameraman maatrame! Theatrical experience theppinchaadu ! Hats off! Malli, women empowerment dialogues kooda over gaa untadhi. Aa dialogues vinte satisfied kaavadam atu unchithe . Ammailu vinte inkaa pogaru gaa aipothaaru . Abbailu aithe mandipothaaru . Avi aadavaallu em thakkuva kaaru ani kaakundaa, magaadu chaep aadadhanikante, anelaa untai. Meeru, ee movie inkaa choosindaka pothe assalu choodadhu! Final gaa ee movie ki naa rating 2.5 / 5 Thank you guys, See you again!

sentence: Thanks for your excellent review . I do disagree with about the 1st scene with Little Diana . Though the camera and the thrills are great there 's no payoff anywhere else in the film on the `` lesson `` she is supposed to have internalized by that episode , that irked me . Yes we might say her wanting to reunite with a dead Steve Trevor might be considered `` taking a shortcut `` , but it does n't wash . I did n't like the overall tone of the movie as well , it tries to be way too preachy instead of focusing on tried / tested superhero antics , for example , even in Spider-Man 2 or even Dark Knight there 's messaging but it should be show not tell , but we ca n't deny the fact that Gal Gadot rules as Wonder Woman .
translation: Thanks for your excellent review. I do disagree with about the 1st scene with Little Diana. Although the camera and the thrills are great there's no payoff anywhere else in the film on the ``lesson'' she is supposed to have internalized by that episode, that irked me. Yes we might say her wanting to reunite with a dead Steve Trevor might be considered ``taking a shortcut'', but it doesn't wash. I did n't like the overall tone of the movie as well, it tries to be way too preachy instead of focusing on tried / tested superhero antics, for example, even in Spider-Man 2 or even Dark Knight there's messaging but it should be show not tell, but we can't deny the fact that Gal Gadot rules as Wonder Woman.

sentence: @Ravi Kiran Vedula that â€™ s what I mean , like these â€œ inspirational â€ movies often dramatize the characters , like you said . For example , they â€™ ll make the main lead extra hard working and overly moral and make them unrealistically good . And they â€™ ll make the villains unrealistically bad with all these traits . It makes the movie very shallow and boring for me cause most of them are this way . And the story won â€™ t even be different . Same story , main lead has idea , some bad guys opposes , she does it anyways fails somehow and wants to give up , someone gives her a lecture to not give up , she does something and wins . and in between there â€™ s some love story . This movie was geared to inspire women , so all these things will be about women empowerment somehow . Haven â€™ t seen it but I bet even she gives a speech at the end about women . Similar to Srimanthudu / Maharishi , where Mahesh Babu is overly good and everything about the movie is geared towards giving back . If I remember he gives a speech I â€™ m that too . translation: @Ravi Kiran Vedula that's what I mean, like these â€œinspirationalâ€ movies often dramatize the characters, like you said. For example, they'll make the main lead extra hard working and overly moral and make them unrealistically good. And they'll make the villains unrealistically bad with all these traits. It makes the movie very shallow and boring for me cause most of them are this way. And the story won't even be different. Same story, main lead has idea, some bad guys opposes, she does it anyways fails somehow and wants to give up, someone gives her a lecture not to give up, she does something and wins. and in between there's some love story. This movie was geared to inspire women, so all these things will be about women empowerment somehow. Haven't seen it but I bet even she gives a speech at the end about women. Similar to Srimanthudu / Maharishi, where Mahesh Babu is overly good and everything about the movie is geared towards giving back. If I remember he gives a speech I'm that too. That's what I meant bro. Like, all these inspirational movies feel the same to me and feel routine and not entertaining and old format, and since this movie is specifically geared to inspire women that's why I said that. Hope I clarified

translation: I watched it yesterday, I usually don't rate or give reviews but as a fan of Chandrasekhar Yeleti, I'm highly disappointed. An unrealistic plot. The above have taken some screentime but they could not take the story forward. If I watch without them, the story will be still the same. Absolutely a loose script, poor editing.
